verbose_text: Given the resemblance between the periodic reoxygenation in IH and IR injury, during which the processes of the overproduction of ROS and the enhancement of inflammatory reactions contribute to organ damage, in study, we aimed to determine whether protein O-GlcNAc levels are related to the impairment in left ventricular (LV) function and the associated pathological hypertrophy in the heart in a rat model prone to the development of hypertension.
